    "body": "Revised title:  Browser field can identify globals to pass in\n\nRevised text:\nIt should as easier to convert existing packages to support browserify and pass in globals:\n\n```\n\"browser\" : [\"./angular.js\", {\"global\":\"angular\"}]\n```\n\nor\n\n```\n\"browser\" : {\n    \"angular\": [ \"./angular.js\", {\"global\":\"angular\"}]\n}\n```\n\nArgument:\nI want to do PRs for packages to support browserify and it would be so much nicer if it was only a one line change to package.json with no added dependencies or files.  If there was a way to identify a global to pass in from the script identified in the browser field, it would make the task of adding support to packages vastly easier.\n",
